The NCAA Men’s Basketball Tournament, known for its fierce competition and unpredictable outcomes, offers key insights into team performance trends. This project will focus on the 2022 and 2023 tournaments, analyzing the relationship between a team’s success and its financial impact. Specifically, factors such as seed, wins, losses, and Final Four appearances will be examined alongside financial data like revenue generated. By exploring how these elements interact, the study aims to better understand the drivers of success in one of collegiate sports’ most celebrated events.
